index.content: index → int (Read Only): The license index in the list.

isEnabled.content: isEnabled → bool (Read Only): True if the license is locally enabled (That is, it has never been disabled).

isRemotelyDisabled.content: isRemotelyDisabled → bool (Read Only): True if the license has been remotely disabled.

key.content: key → str (Read Only): The key sequence.

remoteDisableDate.content: remoteDisableDate → tuple[int, int, int] (Read Only): The date the license was remotely disabled, expressed as a tuple (year, month, day).

status.content: status → int (Read Only): The numeric status code. Negative values indicate the license is not applicable to the current application. A value of zero indicates it does.

statusMessage.content: statusMessage → str (Read Only): A description of the status code.

systemCode.content: systemCode → str (Read Only): The system code associated with this license.

type.content: type → str (Read Only): The license type, e.g. some products being 'Pro', 'Non-Commercial', 'Commercial'. See also app.product in App Class

updateExpiryDate.content: updateExpiryDate → tuple[int, int, int] (Read Only): The date updates for this license expires, expressed as a tuple (year, month, day).

version.content: version → int (Read Only): The numeric license version.
